'''阿布格莱布监狱虐囚事件'''（{{lang-en|Abu Ghraib torture and prisoner abuse}}；{{lang-ar|فضيحة التعذيب في سجن أبو غريب}}），又稱'''美军虐待伊拉克战俘事件'''、'''美英联军虐待伊拉克战俘事件'''或'''虐囚门事件'''，是指[[伊拉克戰爭|伊拉克戰爭]]於2003年爆發初期，[[美军占领伊拉克|美国军队占领伊拉克]]后，[[美軍|美軍]]和[[英軍|英軍]]人员在[[伊拉克|伊拉克]][[巴格達省|巴格達省]][[阿布格莱布监狱|阿布格莱布监狱]]中對伊拉克[[战俘|战俘]]的一系列侵犯[[人權|人權]]行為<ref>{{cite web|last=Greenwald |first=Glenn |url=http://www.salon.com/news/abu_ghraib/2006/03/14/chapter_5/index.html |title=Other government agencies |publisher=Salon.com |accessdate=2012-04-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080212035108/http://www.salon.com/news/abu_ghraib/2006/03/14/chapter_5/index.html |archivedate=2008-02-12 }}</ref>，包含施行[[身體虐待|身體虐待]]、[[性虐待|性虐待]]、[[酷刑|酷刑]]、[[強姦|強姦]]、[[雞姦|雞姦]]和[[謀殺|謀殺]]<ref name='New Yorker 2004-05-17'>{{cite news | first = Seymour M. | last = Hersh | title = Chain of Command | date = 2004-05-17 | url = http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2004/05/17/040517fa_fact2?currentPage=all | work = The New Yorker | accessdate = 2011-09-13 | quote = NBC News later quoted U.S. military officials as saying that the unreleased photographs showed American soldiers "severely beating an Iraqi prisoner nearly to death, having sex with a female Iraqi prisoner, and 'acting inappropriately with a dead body.' The officials said there also was a videotape, apparently shot by U.S. personnel, showing Iraqi guards raping young boys." | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120101055751/http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2004/05/17/040517fa_fact2?currentPage=all | archivedate = 2012-01-01  }}</ref><ref name="Benjamin2009">{{Cite news|first=Mark|last=Benjamin |title=Taguba denies he's seen abuse photos suppressed by Obama: The general told a U.K. paper about images he saw investigating Abu Ghraib – not photos Obama wants kept secret.|url=http://www.salon.com/news/feature/2009/05/30/taguba/|work=Salon.com|date=2008-05-30|accessdate=2009-06-06|quote=The paper quoted Taguba as saying, "These pictures show torture, abuse, rape and every indecency." [...] The actual quote in the Telegraph was accurate, Taguba said – but he was referring to the hundreds of images he reviewed as an investigator of the abuse at Abu Ghraib prison in Iraq| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090611145722/http://www.salon.com/news/feature/2009/05/30/taguba/| archivedate= 2009-06-11 | deadurl= no}}</ref><ref name="hersh2007">{{cite news|quote=Taguba said that he saw "a video of a male American soldier in uniform sodomizing a female detainee"|first=Seymour Myron|last=Hersh|authorlink=Seymour Hersh|title=The general's report: how Antonio Taguba, who investigated the Abu Ghraib scandal, became one of its casualties.|url=http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2007/06/25/070625fa_fact_hersh?printable=true|work=The New Yorker|date=2007-06-25|accessdate=2007-06-17|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070912104000/http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2007/06/25/070625fa_fact_hersh?printable=true|archivedate=2007-09-12}}</ref><ref name="walsh2006">{{cite news|first=Joan |last=Walsh |authorlink=Joan Walsh |author2=Michael Scherer |author3=Mark Benjamin |author4=Page Rockwell |author5=Jeanne Carstensen |author6=Mark Follman |author7=Page Rockwell |author8=Tracy Clark-Flory |title=Other government agencies |url=http://www.salon.com/news/abu_ghraib/2006/03/14/chapter_5/index.html |work=The Abu Ghraib files |publisher=salon.com |date=2006-03-14 |accessdate=2008-02-24 |quote=The Armed Forces Institute of Pathology later ruled al-Jamadi's death a homicide, caused by "blunt force injuries to the torso complicated by compromised respiration." |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080212035108/http://www.salon.com/news/abu_ghraib/2006/03/14/chapter_5/index.html |archivedate=2008-02-12 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。此事件於2004年4月，[[美國|美國]][[CBS新聞|CBS新聞]]公布阿布格莱布監獄內的影像而曝光後，隨即引起全世界關注，並激起浩大的譴責聲浪<ref name="Rush: MPs Just 'Blowing Off Steam'">{{cite news | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2004/05/06/opinion/meyer/main616021.shtml | work=CBS News | title=Rush: MPs Just 'Blowing Off Steam' | date=2004-05-06 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080927205258/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2004/05/06/opinion/meyer/main616021.shtml | archivedate=2008-09-27 }}</ref><ref name="Sontag">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/05/23/magazine/regarding-the-torture-of-others.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm | work=The New York Times | title=Regarding The Torture Of Others | date=2004-05-23 | first=Susan | last=Sontag | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902101726/http://www.nytimes.com/2004/05/23/magazine/regarding-the-torture-of-others.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm | archivedate=2017-09-02 }}</ref>。

==导火线==
美军虐待伊拉克[[战俘|战俘]]问题真正引起全世界震动源自于[[哥伦比亚广播公司|哥伦比亚广播公司]]（CBS）4月28日刊登[[美军|美军]]虐待[[伊拉克|伊拉克]][[囚犯|囚犯]]的[[照片|照片]]，照片显示，一名美军[[宪兵|宪兵]]勒令伊拉克战俘站在箱子上，战俘被蒙上头，手上连着电线。宪兵威胁说，如果战俘从箱子上倒下，就会被电死。另一张照片显示，伊拉克战俘被勒令进行人体堆叠，组成[[金字塔|金字塔]]形状。事件暴露后驻伊美军高级官员表示，美军3月已宣布驻巴格达的美军第800宪兵旅6名成员因虐待大约20名伊战俘将面临[[军事法庭|军事法庭]]审判，美军协助管理战俘的7名军官也将受到纪律处分，包括第800旅最高长官等人。

随着驻伊美军虐待俘虏事件的曝光随即在全球引起包括各国[[政府|政府]]、[[人权组织|人权组织]]和[[新闻媒体|新闻媒体]]的广泛关注。5月3日，[[亚尼斯·卡尔平斯基|亚尼斯·卡尔平斯基]]在接受[[美国广播公司|美国广播公司]][[新闻节目|新闻节目]]《[[早安美国|早安美国]]》采访时说，美国[[宪兵|宪兵]]虐待战俘的事情发生应该共担责任，桑切斯中将难辞其咎。有人猜测美军[[虐待|虐待]]伊拉克[[战俘|战俘]]是美军[[情报|情报]]人员的蓄意行为，[[五角大楼|五角大楼]]高层应该早就知道存在系统的对战俘的虐待行为。

